Third-Party Licenses & Acknowledgments:

*Last updated: April 14, 2026 - v1.4.0 codebase*

This section covers libraries and components that are BUNDLED with UniPlaySong.
External tools (yt-dlp, Deno, FFmpeg) are installed separately by the user and
are not redistributed by this package — their licenses govern the user's
installation directly and are not listed here.

All bundled third-party libraries are used "as-is" without modifications to
their original source code. Native libraries (DLLs) are dynamically linked via
P/Invoke — UniPlaySong does not statically link or incorporate any LGPL code
into its own binary.

.NET Libraries (MIT License):
- HtmlAgilityPack: https://github.com/zzzprojects/html-agility-pack
- Newtonsoft.Json: https://github.com/JamesNK/Newtonsoft.Json
- NAudio: https://github.com/naudio/NAudio
- NVorbis: https://github.com/NVorbis/NVorbis
- FuzzySharp: https://github.com/JakeBayer/FuzzySharp
- MaterialDesignThemes: https://github.com/MaterialDesignInXAML/MaterialDesignInXamlToolkit

Other Licenses:
- TagLibSharp: LGPL v2.1 - https://github.com/mono/taglib-sharp
- SDL2 & SDL2_mixer: zlib License - https://www.libsdl.org/
- zlib (z.dll): zlib License - https://github.com/madler/zlib
- Game Music Emu (gme.dll): LGPL v2.1+ - https://github.com/libgme/game-music-emu
  Copyright (c) Shay Green. Maintained by Vitaly Novichkov and Michael Pyne.
  Used via dynamic linking (P/Invoke to gme.dll distributed as a separate file).
  Built with the Nuked OPN2 YM2612 core (LGPL-safe). The MAME YM2612 core is
  NOT used, which would otherwise make the library GPL v2+.

Reverb Algorithm:
The reverb effect implementation is based on the public domain Freeverb algorithm
by Jezar at Dreampoint (https://ccrma.stanford.edu/~jos/pasp/Freeverb.html).
The algorithm constants and structure follow the libSoX implementation.

Reverb Presets:
The reverb preset values (Acoustic, Ambience, Vocal I, etc.) are derived from
Audacity's factory presets for compatibility purposes. No actual Audacity code
or GPL-licensed software is included or redistributed - only parameter values
and presets are used to shape reverb algorithms. Audacity is licensed under
GPL v2/v3 (https://www.audacityteam.org/).

